Match the following: <image 1>

A. 1-III, 2-IV, 3-I, 4-II
B. 1-II, 2-I, 3-IV, 4-III
C. 1-III, 2-IV, 3-II, 4-I
D. 1-IV, 2-III, 3-II, 4-I

To determine the correct match, let's analyze each option based on the given descriptions:

1. Retailer: Low margin, high volume
   - This matches with Distributor (III) because Distributors are typically retailers.

2. Manufacturer: Does not take title to goods
   - This matches with Manufacturer (II) because Manufacturers do not take title to goods.

3. Distributor: The direct link with the customer
   - This matches with Distributor (III) because Distributors are the direct link with customers.

4. Agent: Gives products to distributors
   - This matches with Agent (IV) because Agents give products to distributors.

So, the correct match is:

A. 1-III, 2-IV, 3-II, 4-I
